header.gameNote: HISPANIC COLLEGE FUND CLASSIC AT HARTFORD CT

article.headline: Fairfield 46, Central Arkansas 43
article.story: HARTFORD, Conn. (AP) -- Greg Nero scored 15 points as Fairfield held off Central Arkansas 46-43 Sunday in the Hispanic College Fund Classic to earn its first victory of the season. Fairfield (1-5) led by as much 13 points in the second half, but Central Arkansas (1-4) fought its way back with tough defense. A LeMar Phillips basket with 2 minutes, 19 seconds left capped a Central Arkansas 16-2 run and cut Fairfield's lead to just 44-43. Central Arkansas missed taking the lead when Frederick Campbell hit the front end of the rim with a fade away jumper with 9.8 seconds left. One free throw each from Marty O'Sullivan (10 points)and Anthony Johnson in the waning seconds sealed the victory for Fairfield. Phillips led Central Arkansas with 11 points, and Durrell Nevels, had nine. The game was low scoring for the first 10 minutes, with neither team getting into the flow offensively. Nero gave Fairfield a 19-15 lead off a no-look pass from Jonathan Han with 4:08 left in the half. It was the start of a 7-2 mini run for Fairfield, which led 24-17 at the half after a Nero basket at the buzzer. Fairfield held Central Arkansas to just 28 percent shooting from the floor, while Fairfield shot 48 percent in the first half. Fairfield finished the tournament 1-2, while the Bears went winless in their three games.
